longName: iShares, Inc. - iShares MSCI Italy ETF
longBusinessSummary: iShares, Inc. - iShares MSCI Italy ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by BlackRock, Inc. It is managed by BlackRock Fund Advisors. The fund invests in public equity markets of Italy. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in growth and value stocks of companies across diversified market capitalization. It seeks to track the performance of the MSCI Italy 25/50 Index, by using representative sampling technique. iShares, Inc. - iShares MSCI Italy ETF was formed on March 12, 1996 and is domiciled in the United States.
